The paper deals with natural language understanding and specifically focuses on gender bias in coreference resolution systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses pre-trained BERT models and fine-tuned representations, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of multiple choice and sequence classification models, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
